to his peaceful human rights activities, in particular his work to defend the rights of the Syrian 
Kurdish community. Further concern was expressed that this attack may constitute part of a trend 
of escalating intimidation and acts of hostility against human rights defenders in Syria.  
 
<b>Urgent appeal 
</b> 
2432. On 23 April 2008, the then Special Representative, together with the Vice-Chairperson of 
the Working Group on Arbitrary Detention, the Special Rapporteur on the independence of 
judges and lawyers, the Special Rapporteur on the promotion and protection of the right to 
freedom of opinion and expression and the Special Rapporteur on the question of torture, sent an 
urgent appeal concerning <b>Mohammed Badih al-Bab</b>, a member of the National Organisation for 
Human Rights in Syria, a non-governmental organization which promotes human rights. 
