<p>2811. In mid-May 2008, three ZESN members were reportedly assaulted by members of the 
Zimbabwe African National Union &#8211; Patriotic Front militia in Mt Darwin East, Mutyandaedza 
village. They were later transported to Mt Darwin District Hospital for treating fractured arms, 
fractured fingers, deep cuts and bruises. However, admission to the hospital was reportedly 
denied to them.  
 
2812. On 21 April 2008, the car of Mr Musaiona Shortgame, parked outside his home in 
Mupandawana Growth Point, was set on fire by three unidentified individuals who ran away 
when Mr Shortgame came out. Mr Shortgame reportedly received a series of death threats prior 
